post_text:
Please take a moment to sign the Change.org petition https://bit.ly/325at4K to recognize the historical significance of Brenda Jones-Smith (1944-2013) to Yolo County.

Born and raised in Woodland, Brenda Jones-Smith was a lifelong advocate for education and students at the local and state level. She served as Trustee on the Woodland Joint Unified School Board from 1977-1993. Jones-Smith also served in leadership roles on the California School Boards Association and the Coalition of California Black School Board Members. She had a 32 year career working for the State of California in the state legislature. (Photo and background courtesy of Yolo County Archives)

shared_text:
Jim Provenza
July 1 at 8:54 PM ¬∑

Tough news: Our Covid-19 cases have almost doubled in the last two weeks. At the current rate, we will exceed 1,000 cases by August. The percentage of positive tests is increasing and hospitalizations are also increasing.

In an effort to curb the spread, we've closed all bars and prohibited indoor dining in restaurants. While this is a tough step back, it's a needed step to ensure that residents from neighboring counties whose bars and indoor dining have been shut down by the state will not congregate here, and above all, to reduce the amount of severe illness and fatalities that inevitably follow these kinds of spikes.

The actions we take in the next month will help shape what life looks like six months from now. Let's work together to make it look as close to "normal" as we can. We are in this together and I know we can do it. I personally look forward to the day when I can sit with my father and give him a hug. I miss him desperately.

Please have a safe and quiet Fourth of July and I will post updates as they come available.

Before you head into the outdoors for this #MemorialDayWeekend ‚Äì please remember to:

Plan Ahead -- Before leaving home, visit the webpage of your local destination to find out if it is open, if parking is available and to learn about the new visitor guidelines.

Stay Local -- Stay close to home. Do not take road trips to parks and beaches.

Stay Safer at 6 ft. ‚Äì Always maintain a physical distance from others. Visitors are being asked to leave if there are too many people to allow for the required physical distance.

Keep Clean ‚Äì Be prepared. Not all restroom are open to the public. Bring soap/sanitizer and pack out all trash.

You can find more details here: https://bit.ly/2Zis202

YOLOFOODBANK.ORG
Home Covid-19 - Yolo Food Bank

Yolo Food Bank
May 18 at 8:33 PM ¬∑

As Yolo County begins a thoughtful, gradual ascent to a new normal in our community, how will we stay well with disease spread still a threat, and economic disaster devastating families and neighbors? Dependable, free access to nutrition will be more important to our residents than ever before, as they strive to thrive. The Yolo Food Bank COVID-19 Relief Fund ensures our response to the already 60% increased demand for food assistance in Yolo County. From Memorial Day to Labor Day, it's estimated that the cost to provide these services will jump another 75% beyond the 75% we've already absorbed in the past two months. Your meaningful gift is urgently needed to ensure food equity in our county as we all continue to weather this storm together. May be count upon you now at https://yolofoodbank.org/donate-covid-19/? Your rapid response will save lives!

March 31 at 4:54 PM ¬∑

Beginning Wednesday, April 1st, families can also pickup Grab-and-Go meals at Yolano Village located on Lemen Avenue off of East Street. Meals can be picked up Monday through Friday from 11am to 1pm at the following 10 locations:
-Gibson, Prairie, Sci-Tech Charter, & Tafoya Elementary Schools
-Douglass & Lee Middle Schools
-Cache Creek, Pioneer, & Woodland High Schools
